Sentencas: In order to elucidate the reaction zone in porous Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95-delta anodes on yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ), ac impedance and steady-state polarization measurements are carried out in H-2-H2O-Ar gas mixtures with different electrode thicknesses, 7, 20, and 45 mu m anodes.
Titulo: Determination of the Reaction Zone in Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Steady-state polarization current becomes larger as the electrode becomes thicker, while the current per unit surface area shows similar value.
Titulo: Determination of the Reaction Zone in Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Therefore, the current seems to be a function of the electrode surface area.
Titulo: Determination of the Reaction Zone in Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In ac impedance measurements, an extremely large pseudo-capacitance is observed to be as large as 10(5)-10(6)
Titulo: Determination of the Reaction Zone in Gadolinia-Doped Ceria Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The measured pseudo-capacitance is caused by the nonstoichiometric perturbation of the oxygen content in the anode material.

Sentencas: Both steady-state polarization and ac impedance measurements suggest that the reaction zone extends from the interface of YSZ/porous Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95-delta anodes toward the outer gas phase.
